<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>The Journey</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="main.css">
 
</head>
<body>
<header>
  <% if (typeof username !== 'undefined') { %>
      <div class="header">
          <h1 class="title">The Journey</h1>
          <div class="profile-section">
              <img src="/images/noprofilephoto.jpg" alt="Profile Photo" class="profile-photo">
              <div class="username-dropdown">
                  <span class="profile-name"><%= username %></span>
                  <div class="dropdown-content">
                      <p><a href="/user">Profile</a></p>
                      <p><a href="/user">Settings</a></p>
                      <p><a href="/user">Logout</a></p>
                  </div>
              </div>
          </div>
      </div>
  <% } else { %>
      <div class="header">
          <p><a href="/login">Login</a></p>
      </div>
  <% } %>
</header>

<div class="container">
  <nav>
      <ul>
          <li><a href="/main">Home</a></li>
          <li><a href="/resources">Resources</a></li>
          <li><a href="/calendar">Calendar</a></li>
          <li><a href="/journal">Journal</a></li>
      </ul>
  </nav>



  <main>
      <section class="welcomeSign">
          <h2>Welcome To The Journey, Where Your Self-Care Journey Begins</h2>
          <p>Here you can keep track and record your thoughts and feelings with support from local resources.</p>
        
      </section>



      <div class="side-by-side-container">
          <!-- Section 1 -->
          <section class="side-section">
              <h2>Daily Affirmation</h2>
              <br>
              <p id="dailyAffrmation"></p>

              
          </section>
           <!-- Section 2 -->
          <section class="side-section">
              <h2>About the Journey</h2>
              <br>
              <p>The website The Journey is all about taking care of one's mental health through self-care. Self-care is taking the time to do things that help you live well and improve your physical and 
                mental health. The Journey provides the space to establish and track your mood and practice mindfulness through journaling and planning your goals. Depending on your specific mood, 
                the Journey provides local resources in Boone, North Carolina. The Journey is made for any and everyone with a focus on the Boone community.</p>
                <br>
                <em><p> Continue your self-care journey here. </p> </em>
                <br>
                <hr>
                <br>
                <p>Created by Tayo Olofintuyi, Crystal Wright, Christiana Wright, Kayla Spruill</p>
      </div>
       <!-- New Section for Tips and Tricks -->
      <section class="tips-section">
          <h2>Tips and Tricks for Journaling</h2>

          <div class="tip">
              <img src="images/Clock.jpg.webp" alt="Clock" class="tip-image">
              <div class="tip-text">
                  <b>1. Find a time that works best for you.</b>
                  <p>Whenever you have free time, start journaling. You can write in the morning to plan your day, reflect on how to handle anticipated events, or focus on what excites you. Try writing at different times to see how it affects your mood.</p>
              </div>
          </div>


          <div class="tip">
              <img src="images/Morrison.jpg" alt="Morrison quote" class="tip-image">
              <div class="tip-text">
                  <b>2. Find quotes that inspire you.</b>
                  <p>When you're feeling stuck, look online for quotes that inspire you. Reflect on how they make you feel and how you can apply them to your life.</p>
              </div>
          </div>


          <div class="tip">
              <img src="images/Talk.jpg" alt="People talking" class="tip-image">
              <div class="tip-text">
                  <b>3. Find someone to write to.</b>
                  <p>When journaling, consider writing to your future self, younger self, someone who has passed, or someone who hurt you.</p>
              </div>
          </div>



          <div class="tip">
              <img src="images/Be Honest.jpg" alt="Be honest" class="tip-image">
              <div class="tip-text">
                  <b>4. Be honest.</b>
                  <p>To get the full benefits of journaling, you need to be honest with yourself. Your journal is a private space, so take the time to be open and honest about your truth.</p>
              </div>
          </div>



          <div class="tip">
              <img src="images/The Journey.jpg" alt="The Journey" class="tip-image">
              <div class="tip-text">
                  <b>5. Enjoy the process.</b>
                  <p>Journaling is a way to practice self-care. Make the journaling process enjoyable and take the time to get to know yourself through writing. Enjoy your journey!</p>
              </div>
          </div>
      </section>
  </main>
</div>




<footer>
  <p>&copy; 2023 The Journey. All rights reserved.</p>
  <p>Contacts</p>
</footer>


</html>

<script>
const dailyAffrmations = [
    "I am in the right place at the right time, doing the right thing ",
    "I am allowed to feel upset, angry, and sad sometimes",
    "I am worthy of receiving good things and of accomplishing my goals in life",
    "I am allowed to take up space, to have desires, and to have a voice",
    "I am capable of making healthy choices",
    "I will surround myself with people who love and support me unconditionally",
    "Growth is sometimes bumpy and isnâ€™t always linear, but I will stay the course"
]

function getRandomDailyAffrmations()
{
    const randomIndex = Math.floor(Math.random() * dailyAffrmations.length);
    return dailyAffrmations[randomIndex];
}

function displayRandomDailyAffrmations()
{
    const dailyAffrmationsElement = document.getElementById("dailyAffrmation");

    if (dailyAffrmationsElement)
    {
        dailyAffrmationsElement.innerText = getRandomDailyAffrmations();
    }
    else
    {
        console.error("Element with ID 'dailyAffrmation' not found.");
    }

   
}

displayRandomDailyAffrmations();</script>
</body>